  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;Title&gt;Children’s A&amp;amp;E and Safari ward&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;My five year old son had a nasty fracture of his elbow just over two weeks ago, and required urgent surgery due to concerns of vascular damage.  I was so appreciative of the care we received in children’s A&amp;amp;E and later on the Safari ward.  A particular nurse in A&amp;amp;E went out of her way to reassure my little boy, and to make sure that his arm was not further damaged during movement around the hospital (there were concerns of the bone piercing the skin).  She checked on us and accompanied us to theatre and I am almost certain that she stayed over her paid hours that evening.  Thank you to this nurse.  The doctors overseeing my son’s operation took time liaising with a central London hospital to take into account his needs, hospital procedures, and also the hospital resources, and explained their decision making to us.  On Safari ward we were again met with kindness and taken care of by another particular nurse.  I want to say thank you to you all for your hard work and care as you made a distressing event much more manageable and we felt our son was genuinely looked after with kindness.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
